## 14. ClawControl Evaluation тАФ Resolved

**Repo:** [jakeledwards/ClawControl](https://github.com/jakeledwards/ClawControl) | **MIT License** | TypeScript (Electron + React + Capacitor) | 181 stars | Active daily commits (as of 2026-03-01)

**Previous assumption was wrong.** The [clawcontrol.dev](https://clawcontrol.dev/) site (referenced in Section 7) gave the impression this was a server-side orchestration tool with kill switches and cryptographic execution envelopes. In reality, `jakeledwards/ClawControl` is a **cross-platform desktop/mobile client** for a single OpenClaw instance. No Docker management, no policy engine, no container lifecycle controls.

### What It Is

A polished Electron + Capacitor client that connects to **one** OpenClaw Gateway via WebSocket (protocol v3). Features:

- Chat UI with real-time LLM streaming (delta + cumulative modes), markdown, code blocks, image send/receive
- Agent dashboard тАФ live grid with status indicators (online/offline/busy), model info, streaming state
- Agent management тАФ create, rename, delete, browse workspace files and config
- Session management тАФ concurrent sessions with per-session stream isolation, subagent spawning
- Cron job CRUD тАФ create, toggle, run, delete scheduled tasks
- Skill management тАФ ClawHub browser with VirusTotal security scan badges, one-click install
- Server config editor тАФ full YAML config read/write via `config.get`/`config.patch` with hash-based conflict detection
- Usage/cost tracking тАФ token/cost charts, activity heatmaps
- Exec approval flow тАФ approve/deny tool execution requests, per-agent allowlist management
- Device pairing тАФ Ed25519 identity, node listing, paired device management
- Voice dictation + wake word detection

### What It Does NOT Have

- **No Docker/container awareness** тАФ zero knowledge of containers, images, or lifecycle
- **No policy engine / gateway** тАФ no deterministic rule evaluation
- **No inter-agent message routing** тАФ no broker concept
- **No agent registry / capability discovery** тАФ just lists agents on a single Gateway
- **No audit logging infrastructure** тАФ no OpenSearch, no append-only guarantees
- **No kill switch** тАФ can delete agents but no container stop + secret rotation
- **No boundary / trust zone concept**
- **No multi-instance orchestration** тАФ connects to ONE OpenClaw server, not a fleet

### Overlap with Command Center (Section 10)

| Command Center View | ClawControl Coverage | Reusable? |
|---|---|---|
| Agent Dashboard / Fleet Map | `AgentDashboard.tsx` тАФ live agent grid with status, model, streaming | Partially тАФ single-server, but tile pattern is reusable |
| LLM Conversation Live Streaming | `ChatArea.tsx` + per-session stream isolation тАФ well-built | **Yes** тАФ streaming architecture (delta/cumulative, source arbitration, tool call cards) is exactly what we need |
| Agent Detail View | `AgentDetailView.tsx` тАФ identity, config files, skills | Partially тАФ no policy/resource/action tabs |
| Cron / Scheduled Workflows | `CronJobDetailView.tsx` + `CreateCronJobView.tsx` тАФ full CRUD | **Yes** тАФ maps to our Scheduled Workflows view |
| Server Config Editor | `ServerSettingsView.tsx` тАФ dirty tracking, minimal patch, conflict detection | **Yes** тАФ pattern directly applicable to Kubex Configuration Manager |
| Usage / Cost Tracking | `UsageView.tsx` тАФ token/cost charts, activity heatmaps | Partially тАФ single-agent scope, chart patterns reusable |
| Skill Management | Full ClawHub browser with security badges, install flow | **Yes** тАФ directly useful for managing Kubex skills |
| Exec Approval Flow | `nodes.ts` тАФ approve/deny execution, allowlist management | Partially тАФ maps to Approval Queue concept, scoped to exec only |
| Inter-Agent Message View | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Approval Queue (Gateway) | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Kill Switch / Control Panel | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Workflow Manager (chain viz) | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Audit & Investigation | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Boundary Management | **None** | Build from scratch |
| Infrastructure Health | **None** | Build from scratch |

### Decision: Extract, Don't Adopt

**Do NOT adopt ClawControl wholesale as our Command Center.** It's architecturally a single-server client; refactoring into a multi-fleet operator console would be as much work as building new.

**DO extract these pieces into the Command Center:**

1. **OpenClaw WebSocket client library** (`src/lib/openclaw/`) тАФ production-quality, typed, handles streaming, reconnection, auth, concurrent sessions. This is exactly how our Command Center backend talks to each Kubex's Gateway. Fork into `services/command-center/frontend/src/lib/`.
2. **Per-session stream isolation architecture** тАФ the `SessionStreamState` pattern with source arbitration, cumulative text merging, and subagent detection is non-trivial and directly maps to watching multiple Kubexes simultaneously.
3. **Design system** (`DESIGN_SPEC.md`) тАФ thorough color system, typography, layout, responsive breakpoints, animations. Adopt as our Command Center's visual foundation.
4. **Cron job UI** тАФ almost 1:1 with our Scheduled Workflows view. Port directly.
5. **Config editor patterns** тАФ dirty tracking, minimal JSON merge patch, hash-based conflict detection, post-save reconnect handling. Apply to Kubex Configuration Manager.
6. **Skill browser / ClawHub integration** тАФ useful for managing skills across Kubexes.

**Estimated work saved:** ~20-30% of the Command Center frontend effort. Zero impact on backend services (Gateway, Kubex Manager, Broker, Registry тАФ which remain the bulk of the work).

### Key Technical Details (for extraction)

**Protocol:** Custom frame-based JSON-RPC over WebSocket (v3). Frames: `req` (clientтЖТserver), `res` (serverтЖТclient), `event` (server push). Auth via Ed25519 device identity or bearer token.

**Key RPC methods we'll use:**
- `sessions.list`, `sessions.spawn`, `chat.send`, `chat.history`, `chat.abort`
- `agents.list`, `agent.identity.get`, `agents.files.list`
- `config.get`, `config.patch`
- `skills.status`, `skills.update`, `skills.install`
- `cron.list`, `cron.get`, `cron.update`, `cron.add`
- `exec.approvals.get`, `exec.approval.resolve`

**Streaming events:**
- `chat { state: "delta" | "final" }` тАФ message streaming
- `agent { stream: "assistant" | "tool" | "lifecycle" }` тАФ agent activity
- `presence` тАФ online/offline status

**State management:** Zustand store with localStorage persistence. Per-session streaming maps (`streamingSessions`, `sessionToolCalls`) enable concurrent agent conversations.

